natural problem: How many prime positive integers are divisors of 555?
natural solution: When we find the prime factorization of 555, we end up with $3\cdot5\cdot37$, which means we have $\boxed{3}$ prime positive divisors.

fixes primes :: "nat set"
assumes h0 : "primes = {p. prime p \<and> p dvd 555}"
shows  "card primes = 3"
